related_questions.question: What is a cider?
related_questions.snippet: Cider is an alcoholic beverage made from fermenting apple juice. The word carries this same meaning in England, Canada and through its variations in France (“Cidre”) and Spain (“Sidra”). Cider was easily the most common alcoholic beverage in colonial America.
related_questions.title: What is cider anyway? - Number 12 Cider

related_questions.question: Is cider any good for you?
related_questions.snippet: Drinking cider can also help boost your energy levels, thanks to the natural sugars found in the beverage. Cider is also a great source of vitamins, minerals, and fiber. The vitamin content found in cider may help improve your overall health and boost your immune system.
related_questions.title: Is Cider good for you? The benefits and drawbacks revealed

related_questions.question: Is cider an alcohol?
related_questions.snippet: Cider is an alcoholic drink made by fermenting apples. It can be still or sparkling. Perry is a similar drink, made using the same method, but using pears instead of apples. It's the third most bought alcoholic drink for consumption at home, after beer and wine.
